ou ALWAYS carry with you.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br>Jboots.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Q: Was the warrior class the first character you seriously played?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br>Yes, and the only class, really. I've got a 21 druid, but I haven't gotten exp with her in months.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Q: I'm sure you have had plenty of fun throughout, but what particular moment really stood out that made you cackle evilly at your own power?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br>When I tanked Nagafen throughout 90% of the fight. I stood up to a dragon and *lived*. Since then, everything has pretty much been a progression of that.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Q: If you could add one spell type or ability to the Everquest warrior class, what would it be?(just ONE hehe)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br>One spell, just a straight up stun. Give it a long cast time, a mana cost of 20, and cap a warrior's mana pool at 40 or so. In normal exp groups, with any form of clarity, you'd have enough mana to break mezz with stun. That's all I want.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Q: Do you solo regularly?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br>Yes.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Q: If you could trade your warrior character for any other class of the same level and relatively equal gear, would you?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br>No. The novelty of playing another class would fade quickly for me. <p><html><body><p style="font-size:110%"><b><a href="http://www.suckbird.com/roster/profile.asp?who=Iskandar" STYLE="text-decoration: none"  target="_blank">Veteran Iskandar Alazeem</a><br><a href=http://www.steelwarrior.org STYLE="text-decoration: none" target="_blank">Steel Warrior</a> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior STYLE="text-decoration: none"  target="_blank">moderator</a><br><a href=http://www.keepersofthefaith.org STYLE="text-decoration: none"  target="_blank">Keepers of the Faith</a></b>