May 7 2000<br><br>Q: Why did you choose the warrior class? Do you always play one in RPGs or were there other reasons?<br>I generally play melee classes.  Usually its a Ranger of some sort.  I actually got EQ in April of 1999 and started a Ranger.  But after some hours of play it was so hard and there was no documentation that I gave it up until Kunark came out.  When I started up again, I choose a Warrior because it told me that it would be the easiest class to play.  (actually Human Warrior was the easiest combo)  Since my past experience was so difficult, I figured I'd go with that until I got the hang of the game.  Heh, 2 years later I'm still going with it ).  <br><br>Q: When did you feel like you had &quot;mastered&quot; the warrior class, given the abilities you had available at the time?<br>Never.  I'm always learning and always getting better. <br><br>Q: What is your favorite weapon (for fun reason or whatever) overall?<br>What I'm using now.  They are the best weapons I've ever had.  Anything that taunts well and kills fast.  In my earlier days, I felt uber when I landed a Mithril 2 Handed staff!  That was my favorite weapon for a long time.  <br><br>Q: Name one item you ALWAYS carry with you.<br>A Flower of Fiona Vie that someone gave me long ago.  I consider it good luck. <br><br><br>Q: Was the warrior class the first character you seriously played?<br>Yes.<br><br><br>Q: I'm sure you have had plenty of fun throughout, but what particular moment really stood out that made you cackle evilly at your own power?<br>Well, I don't cackle evilly as a Warrior.  But one great time was when I got to tank Velk.  (I was never MT)  Getting beat on, the CHs coming in, the guild saying &quot;Go Drac!&quot;, it was a RUSH!.  <br><br>Q: If you could add one spell type or ability to the Everquest warrior class, what would it be?(just ONE hehe)<br>Hmmm.  The only thing I can think of off hand is to make some AA ability or just make a level 60 ability that all non-Ogre warriors can no longer be stunned from the front. <br><br>Q: Do you solo regularly?<br>No.  Its ineffecient even when well equipped, and boring.<br><br><br>Q: If you could trade your warrior character for any other class of the same level and relatively equal gear, would you?<br>No, I'm quite happy with my Warrior and I've worked hard for what he has.  I'd never give him up.<br><br> If I had to choose though, I'd probably a rogue or a monk.  Really you don't need that many Warriors on a raid.  In terms of melee damage, you really need well equipped, Monks, Rogues, Ranger, and SKs and Pallys to a degree.  But if I was going to trade in my Warrior it would be for either the highest melee damage dealer, Rogue, or one of the best pullers and damage dealers, Monk.  <br><br> <p><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=127089">Dracillion of Qeynos</a><BR>Warlord<BR>Bertox</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udracillionofqeynos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DracillionofQeynos</A> at: 4/4/02 10:26:30 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwarlordbalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Warlord Balker</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.mindspring.com/~goodonion/_uimages/BalkinRed2.JPG" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/4/02 12:05:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=628.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Interview with a warrior (grabbed from graffe's)</span><hr size=1> Q: When was your warrior born?<br><br>&gt; June 2000<br><br>Q: Why did you choose the warrior class? Do you always play one in RPGs or were there other reasons?<br><br>&gt; I chose the warrior because I like the idea of being in the middle of everything going on.  I like the &quot;Warrior Attitude.&quot;  An example of the &quot;Warrior Attitude&quot; at the beginning of March a friend scheduled a Chardok Royals raid, he sent a + Chardok mage down to King's hallway and CoH'd everyone down.  At the end of March I scheduled a Chardok Royals raid, the same mage was available to me, but I chose to do it the right way, the warrior way, fight down and kill everything that crosses my path, that, in my opinion, is the &quot;Warrior Attitude&quot; that I love.<br><br>Q: When did you feel like you had &quot;mastered&quot; the warrior class, given the abilities you had available at the time?<br><br>&gt; Hrmmm, I think I started grasping the concept of what a warrior is early on, tho, I didn't master the class until I was in my 50's hunting in Sebilis.  Actually, I still don't think I've mastered it, I'm still learning something new every day.<br><br>Q: What is your favorite weapon (for fun reason or whatever) overall?<br><br>&gt; Right now it's my epic since it's still new to me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Q: Name one item you ALWAYS carry with you.<br><br>&gt; Up until recently I've always carried Frost Giant Steaks, they add the little bit of Sta and Str.  But, being careless, I forgot to move them back down below my regular food, and I ate 'em.  I'm also always carrying my resist gear, my Katta EB necklace, my bow/Idol of the Fallen, my T-Boots, and a bunch of runes for my wizard friend who likes to collect 'em.<br><br>Q: Was the warrior class the first character you seriously played?<br><br>&gt; Yes and No.  My very first character was an Ogre Warrior.  I got him to level 23 and quit playing because 1) I forgot to distribute my starting stat points 2) Ogre warriors are a dime a dozen, I wanted something not so common.